cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use PathClaw in your research, please cite it as below."
title: "PathClaw: Computational Pathology Platform with Agentic Workflows"
abstract: >
  PathClaw is a research platform for computational pathology that combines
  whole-slide image preprocessing, multiple-instance learning model training,
  genomic analysis, and an in-app LLM agent with tool use. It supports gated
  HuggingFace backbones (UNI, CONCH, Virchow, GigaPath), MIL methods (ABMIL,
  CLAM, TransMIL, DSMIL, RRTMIL, WIKG), TCGA/GDC integration, cBioPortal
  queries, and per-session manuscript authoring.
type: software
